4. Afro Genie’s Three-Tier Licensing Framework
Tier 1 – Licensed API (Musixmatch Integration)
Purpose:
To provide Afro Genie with legally licensed lyric data, translations, and metadata through Musixmatch, the world’s largest authorized lyrics and music metadata platform.
Actions:
Subscribe to the Musixmatch Developer Plan at US$29.50 per month.
Integrate the Musixmatch API to retrieve:
Up to 500 API calls per day (standard limit).
Static lyrics and basic lyric translations for display within Afro Genie.
Comprehensive music metadata — artist names, album details, genres, ISRC/track IDs, and release dates.


No caching or offline storage of full lyric text; all displays must be served dynamically via the API.


Attribute every displayed lyric as required by Musixmatch:

 “Lyrics provided by Musixmatch. © Respective owners.”


Advantages:
Immediate access to the largest global lyric and translation catalog (over 8 million tracks).
Includes major Afrobeat and international catalogs already cleared through publishers and CMOs.
Provides reliable metadata synchronization and verified lyric text.
Ensures Afro Genie’s full legal compliance for public lyric display and translation.
Limitations:
Subscription fee: US $29.50 per month (developer tier).
Daily cap: 500 API calls.
No permanent lyric caching or redistribution permitted under Musixmatch API Terms of Use.
Cheaper alternative: https://rapidapi.com/Glavier/api/genius-song-lyrics1/pricing
Tier 2 – Direct Publisher / Label Licensing
Purpose:
Secure exclusive, region-specific lyric display and translation rights from African publishers, labels, or administrators.
Implementation:
Execute Afro Genie Lyric & Translation License Agreement.
Rights granted:
Non-exclusive license to display, store, and translate lyrics.
Advantages:
Full control over data storage and translations.
Builds proprietary African lyric catalogue.
Compliance Safeguards:
All agreements are stored with metadata.
Attribution and rights tags are displayed on lyric pages.


Tier 3 – Artist-Contributed Lyrics (Emerging Artist Gateway)
Purpose:
Empower emerging and independent African artists to directly upload, verify, and control their own lyrics — reducing reliance on third-party licensors.
